   Sponsor Message

   [69]Book covers of: Flesh; I See You've Called In Dead; The Usual
   Desire to Kill; Vera Wong's Guide to Snooping (on a Dead Man)
   NPR

[70]6 tales of mystery and mishap to dive into this weekend

   [71]April 1, 2025  New on the shelves this week: An obit writer writes
   — and drunkenly publishes — his own obituary. A Hungarian teen stumbles
   into adulthood. And geriatric sleuth Vera Wong returns.

   [72]Book Covers: Elphie by Gregory Maguire, Free by Amanda Knox, Tilt
   by Emma Pattee, Twist by Colum McCann, Yoko by David Sheff
   NPR

[73]New books this week: Yoko, Elphaba, Amanda Knox and lost connections

   [74]March 25, 2025  This week's new releases include a memoir from
   Amanda Knox reflecting on her murder case and exoneration, a biography
   of Yoko Ono, new fiction from Column McCann, and the latest Wicked book
   Elphie.

   [75]Book covers of Abundance, The Buffalo Hunter Hunter, The Mysterious
   Mr. Nakamoto, Sunrise on the Reaping and Theft
   NPR

[76]New books this week: 'Hunger Games' is back, and young people navigate a
new Tanzania

   [77]March 18, 2025  This week brings a number of promising new reads —
   but none more eagerly awaited than Sunrise on the Reaping. We offer 5
   books to consider picking up.

   [78]All the Other Mothers Hate Me by Sarah Harman, The Antidote by
   Karen Russell, Care and Feeding by Laurie Woolever, Stag Dance by
   Torrey Peters, and The Story of Witches by Willow Winsham
   NPR

[79]New books this week: A foodie memoir, a missing child, witches
illustrated, and more

   [80]March 11, 2025  Care and Feeding chronicles life in the culinary
   world. All the Other Mothers Hate Me follows a mom turned amateur
   detective. Plus, Karen Russell's first full-length novel since
   Swamplandia!

